WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.600 --> 00:00:11.808
Of the four recommendations, this is the one built purely
to keep you alive. Safest. Here's what it does, and
exactly when you should pick it.

2
00:00:12.408 --> 00:00:21.216
It's the second card in Step two. Safest bets only a small
slice of your edge, roughly a quarter Kelly. The entire
goal here is survival, not speed.

3
00:00:21.816 --> 00:00:36.192
It hunts for the setup with the lowest bust rate and the
shallowest drawdown, among setups that still have a real
edge. Notice it usually picks the smallest position size,
and it'll sometimes even turn the stop off, because at
this tiny size, it doesn't need one.

4
00:00:36.792 --> 00:00:49.224
The tradeoff is patience. It is slow. It takes the most
days to reach a target, and the dollar result per run is
the smallest of the four. You are deliberately trading
away speed for the near-certainty that you will not blow
up.

5
00:00:49.824 --> 00:01:04.128
So who is this for? Anyone on a funded account they cannot
afford to lose. Anyone who hates paying for resets. Or
anyone early in their journey who just needs to survive
long enough to actually learn. When ruin is the real
enemy, this is your card.

6
00:01:04.728 --> 00:01:12.288
Safest. Slow, durable, and almost unkillable. The right
pick when staying in the game matters more than growing
fast.
